data.content:
Three breaking changes affect your code:

---

### 1. `ExecuteUpdateAsync` ŌĆö now takes `Func`, not `Expression`

Your expression tree code **won't compile** because the overload now expects a regular lambda. Replace the entire block with:

```csharp
await context.Blogs.ExecuteUpdateAsync(s =>
{
    s.SetProperty(b => b.Views, 8);
    if (nameChanged)
    {
        s.SetProperty(b => b.Name, "foo");
    }
});
```

No more manual `Expression.Call`/`Expression.Lambda` needed ŌĆö this was the whole motivation for the change.

---

### 2. Complex type column names ŌĆö now auto-uniquified & nested paths changed

Two sub-changes:

- **Duplicate names get a numeric suffix.** If both `ShippingAddress.Street` and `BillingAddress.Street` previously shared a `Street` column (silent and data-corrupting), EF 10 generates `Street` and `Street1`.
- **Nested complex types use full path.** `Order.Payment.BillingAddress.City` was `BillingAddress_City`, now becomes `Payment_BillingAddress_City`.

If you have an existing database, **pin the old column names** to avoid a migration diff:

```csharp
modelBuilder.Entity<Customer>(b =>
{
    b.ComplexProperty(c => c.ShippingAddress, p =>
        p.Property(a => a.Street).HasColumnName("Street"));
    b.ComplexProperty(c => c.BillingAddress, p =>
        p.Property(a => a.Street).HasColumnName("Street"));
});

// For nested complex types, pin each property:
modelBuilder.Entity<Order>()
    .ComplexProperty(o => o.Payment)
    .ComplexProperty(p => p.BillingAddress)
    .Property(a => a.City)
    .HasColumnName("BillingAddress_City");
```

---

### 3. `IRelationalCommandDiagnosticsLogger` ŌĆö new `logCommandText` parameter

Every method gains a `string logCommandText` parameter (contains potentially-redacted SQL for logging). Add it:

```csharp
public class MyLogger : IRelationalCommandDiagnosticsLogger
{
    public InterceptionResult<DbDataReader> CommandReaderExecuting(
        IRelationalConnection connection,
        DbCommand command,
        DbContext context,
        Guid commandId,
        Guid connectionId,
        DateTimeOffset startTime,
        string logCommandText)   // ŌåÉ new parameter
    {
        // Use logCommandText for logging (redacted),
        // command.CommandText for actual SQL
    }
}
```

Update all other methods on the interface the same way (`CommandReaderExecuted`, `CommandScalarExecuting`, etc.).
